%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20axed%20CEO%20and%20co-founder%20of%20a%20San%20Francisco-based%20tech%20company%20has%20been%20accused%20in%20a%20bombshell%20lawsuit%20of%20forcing%20his%20former%20executive%20assistant%20to%20sign%20a%20%26quot%3Bslave%20contract%26quot%3B%20and%20subjecting%20her%20to%20multiple%20years%20of%20%26quot%3Bsexual%20abuse%2C%20torture%20and%20assault.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiff%2C%20only%20identified%20as%20%26quot%3BJane%20Doe%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20suit%20filed%20last%20week%20in%20a%20California%20court%2C%20says%20in%20the%20court%20documents%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftradeshift-looks-to-solve-late-payment-problem-2014-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformer%20Tradeshift%20CEO%20Christian%20Lanng%3C%2Fa%3E%20sexually%20trafficked%20her%20around%20the%20world%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20business%20trips%20for%20the%20fintech%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20alleges%20that%20Lanng%20made%20the%20woman%20sign%20the%20%26quot%3Bshocking%20and%20repulsive%26quot%3B%20sex%20%26quot%3Bslave%20contract%26quot%3B%20that%20named%20him%20as%20%26quot%3Bmaster%26quot%3B%20several%20months%20into%20her%20employment%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhsbc-partners-with-fintech-tradeshift-on-financing-product-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETradeshift%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20causing%20her%20work%20and%20personal%20life%20to%20spiral%20into%20%26quot%3Ba%20dark%20abyss%20of%20unwanted%20sexual%20horror.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20abuse%20she%20endured%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says%2C%20included%20the%20woman%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20bound%20against%20her%20will%20and%20beaten%20to%20the%20point%20of%20bleeding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiff%20claims%20in%20the%20suit%20that%20she%20was%20fired%20in%20May%202020%20after%20she%20complained%20to%20the%20company's%20human%20resources%20department%2C%20its%20co-founders%20and%20members%20of%20its%20board%20of%20directors%20%26quot%3Babout%20the%20rape%2C%20sexual%20abuse%2C%20torture%20and%20assault%20she%20was%20suffering%20at%20the%20hands%26quot%3B%20of%20Laang%20under%20the%20%26quot%3Bslave%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELanng%20%E2%80%94%20who%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftradeshift.com%2Fresources%2Fpress%2Fleadership-change-october-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efired%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Tradeshift%20this%20past%20September%20for%20what%20the%20company%20called%20%26quot%3Bgross%20misconduct%20on%20multiple%20grounds%26quot%3B%20that%20included%20%26quot%3Ballegations%20of%20sexual%20assault%20and%20harassment%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20vehemently%20denied%20the%20accusations%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20against%20him%20in%20a%20lengthy%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20Lanng%2C%20who%20did%20not%20dispute%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bslave%20contract%2C%26quot%3B%20claimed%20that%20he%20and%20his%20accuser%20were%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bconsensual%20sexual%20relationship%26quot%3B%20before%20he%20hired%20her%20at%20Tradeshift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELanng%20said%20their%20relationship%20ended%20eight%20months%20after%20she%20joined%20the%20company.%20Business%20Insider%20obtained%20a%20screenshot%20of%20an%20email%20exchange%20between%20Lanng%20and%20the%20plaintiff%2C%20which%20shows%20Lanng%20sharing%20a%20Google%20Doc%20entitled%20%26quot%3BSlave%20Contract%26quot%3B%20with%20his%20assistant%20in%20April%202014%20%E2%80%94%20about%20four%20months%20after%20her%20lawyers%20say%20she%20was%20hired%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20shocking%20and%20vile%20claims%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20are%20categorically%20false%2C%20and%20I%20reject%20allegations%20that%20I%20subjected%20someone%20to%20any%20form%20of%20abuse%20during%20my%20tenure%20as%20CEO%20or%20at%20any%20other%20time%20of%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Lanng%20said%20in%20the%20statement%2C%20calling%20his%20decision%20to%20hire%20someone%20he%20was%20dating%20a%20%26quot%3Bgrave%20error%20of%20judgment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Tradeshift%20CEO%20said%20that%20his%20accuser%20worked%20at%20the%20company%20for%20five%20more%20years%20after%20their%20relationship%20ended%20and%20that%20her%20position%20was%20later%20eliminated%20in%20a%20round%20of%20layoffs.%20He%20called%20her%20accusations%20%26quot%3Ba%20cynical%20and%20callous%20affront%20to%20victims%20of%20sexual%20violence%20and%20human%20trafficking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiff's%20attorneys%2C%20Bryan%20Freedman%20and%20Miles%20Cooley%2C%20blasted%20Lanng's%20comments%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20what%20world%20is%20a%20slave%20contract%20between%20a%20CEO%20and%20his%20employee%20remotely%20consensual%3F%20That%20Lanng%20is%20misrepresenting%20timelines%20and%20duration%20of%20the%20abuse%20to%20excuse%20his%20behavior%20is%20truly%20reprehensible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20client%20entirely%20rejects%20the%20notion%20that%20she%20had%20a%20'consensual'%20slave%20relationship%20with%20her%20boss%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawyers%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20if%20the%20allegations%20are%20not%20horrific%20enough%2C%20the%20corporate%20coverup%20and%20malfeasance%20as%20alleged%20in%20the%20complaint%20takes%20this%20tragedy%20to%20another%20sick%20level.%C2%A0%20We%20look%20forward%20to%20setting%20forth%20all%20the%20facts%20in%20the%20course%20of%20discovery%20and%20litigation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attorneys%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20their%20client%20started%20her%20employment%20at%20Tradeshift%20in%20January%202014%20and%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bslave%20contract%26quot%3B%20began%20in%20April%20of%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiff%20says%20in%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20also%20names%20Tradeshift%20as%20a%20defendant%2C%20that%20Lanng's%20%26quot%3Bhorrific%20treatment%26quot%3B%20of%20her%20was%20%26quot%3Bknown%20by%20and%20tacitly%20approved%20of%20by%20Tradeshift's%26quot%3B%20other%20founders%20and%20board%20of%20directors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20describes%20Tradeshift%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btoxic%2C%20hostile%20work%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20alleges%20that%20the%20plaintiff%20was%20also%20sexually%20abused%20by%20former%20Tradeshift%20board%20members%20Morten%20Lund%20and%20Morten%20Sondergaard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELund%20and%20Sondergaard%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20by%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Tradeshift%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bdenies%20the%20allegations%20in%20the%20claim%20insofar%20as%20they%20are%20made%20against%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Lanng's%20statement%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20co-founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Tradeshift%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20I%20want%20to%20be%20very%20clear%3A%20Tradeshift%20never%20condoned%20or%20concealed%20sexual%20harassment%20claims.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20alleges%20that%20the%20plaintiff%20has%20undergone%20%26quot%3Bphysical%2C%20psychological%20and%20emotional%20trauma%20and%20harm%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20sex%20abuse%20she%20endured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-tech-ceo-accused-forcing-assistant-sex-slave-contract-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702504680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a28d47a3c8094d5dcbff9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-tech-ceo-accused-forcing-assistant-sex-slave-contract-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20lawsuit%20says%20CEO%20Christian%20Lanng%20made%20the%20woman%20sign%20the%20%26quot%3Bshocking%20and%