vated%20the%20canister%2C%20releasing%20thick%20yellow%20smoke.%20The%20two%20were%20arrested%2C%20so%20were%20three%20others.%20One%20person%20who%20was%20allegedly%20part%20of%20the%20conspiracy%2C%20is%20on%20the%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20the%20Speaker%2C%20Om%20Birla%2C%20moved%20a%20request%20to%20the%20Home%20Ministry%20through%20the%20Secretary%20General%20for%20a%20probe%20into%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Deputy%20Speaker%2C%20by%20convention%2C%20heads%20and%20manages%20the%20security%20aspects%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%202001%20parliament%20attack%20--%20when%2015%20people%2C%20including%20five%20terrorists%2C%20died%20--%20the%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20formed%20to%20deal%20with%20it%2C%20was%20headed%20by%20then%20Deputy%20Speaker%2C%20Congress's%20PM%20Sayeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20Somnath%20Chatterjee's%20tenure%20as%20the%20Speaker%2C%20when%20Charanjit%20Singh%20Atwal%20was%20his%20Deputy%2C%20many%20mock%20security%20drills%20were%20held.%20So%20much%20so%20it%20drew%20flak%20from%20the%20government%20and%20MPs%2C%20who%20criticised%20Mr%20Chatterjee%20for%20allowing%20security%20drills%20when%20parliament%20was%20in%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20parliament%20was%20shut%20down%20and%20adjourned%20for%20a%20while%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20some%20security-related%20intelligence%20inputs%20from%20the%20American%20consulate%20in%20Chennai.%20The%20information%2C%20however%2C%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20hoax.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20parliament%20building%20was%20expected%20to%20address%20all%20security%20concerns%20and%20meet%20the%20parameters%20for%20the%2021st%20Century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20found%20not%20to%20even%20have%20body%20scanner%20machines%2C%20which%20are%20present%20in%20airports%20of%20the%20country.%20These%20machines%20will%20now%20be%20installed%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELate%20this%20evening%2C%20the%20Union%20Home%20Ministry%20ordered%20a%20high-level%20inquiry%20into%20the%20incident%20following%20a%20call%20by%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla.%20A%20full-fledged%20probe%20is%20expected%20to%20address%20the%20security%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702492800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fkrkdfm8_parliament-smoke-attack_625x300_13_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flok-sabha-security-breach-no-deputy-speaker-to-secure-parliament-centre-orders-probe-into-breach-4669083%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20parliamentary%20convention%20and%20a%20constitution%20requirement%20that%20Lok%20Sabha%20has%20a%20deputy%20speaker.%20But%20this%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20which%20is%20nearing%20the%20end%20of%20its%20tenure%2C%20never%20had%20one.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flok-sabha-security-breach-no-deputy-speaker-to-secure-parliament-centre-orders-probe-into-breach-4669083%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flok-sabha-security-breach-no-deputy-speaker-to-secure-parliament-centre-orders-probe-into-breach-4669083%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flok-sabha-security-breach-no-deputy-speaker-to-secure-parliament-centre-orders-probe-into-breach-4669083%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SRK%20convinced%20Rakesh%20to%20cast%20him%20in%20King%20Uncle%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702492720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105970495%2Cimgsize-41292.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshah-rukh-khan-convinced-rakesh-roshan-to-cast-him-in-king-uncle-instead-of-salman-khan-reveals-his-close-friend-vivek-vaswani%2Farticleshow%2F105970537.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105970537.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20recent%20interview%2C%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan's%20close%20friend%20and%20producer%20Vivek%20Vaswani%20recalled%20how%20the%20superstar%20left%20Rakesh%20Roshan%20stunned%20with%20his%20knowledge%20of%20film%20business%20and%20landed%20a%20role%20in%20King%20Uncle%20in%20place%20of%20Salman%20Khan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshah-rukh-khan-convinced-rakesh-roshan-to-cast-him-in-king-uncle-instead-of-salman-khan-reveals-his-close-friend-vivek-vaswani%2Farticleshow%2F105970537.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Canada%20Signals%20Growing%20Moral%20Discomfort%20Among%20Israel's%20Friends%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20opposed%20to%20an%20abstention%20in%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%20on%20October%2027%20related%20to%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%2C%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20one%20on%20December%2012.%20A%20slight%20difference%20in%20the%20wording%20of%20the%20resolutions%20as%20well%20as%20the%20UN%20Secretary%20General%20Antonio%20Guterres%20invoking%20Article%2099%20seem%20to%20have%20affected%20the%20overall%20change.%20Though%20Article%2099%20pertains%20specifically%20to%20the%20UNSC%20where%20the%20Secretary%20General%20can%20%26quot%3Bbring%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Security%20Council%20any%20matter%20which%20in%20his%20opinion%20may%20threaten%20the%20maintenance%20of%20international%20peace%20and%20security%26quot%3B.%20The%20UNSC%20resolution%20on%20Friday%20was%20vetoed%20by%20the%20US%2C%20a%20permanent%20member%20but%20it%20appears%20to%20have%20had%20an%20effect%20with%20the%20overwhelming%20numbers%20voting%20in%20favour%20in%20UNGA%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20resolution%20on%20Tuesday%20in%20UNGA%20called%20for%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%2C%20as%20well%20as%20immediate%20and%20unconditional%20release%20of%20all%20hostages%26quot%3B%3B%20however%2C%20the%20one%20on%20October%2027%20didn't%20specifically%20mention%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bhostages%26quot%3B%20though%20it%20did%20say%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20and%20unconditional%20release%20of%20all%20civilians%20held%20captive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20the%20resolution%20on%20Tuesday%20made%20a%20very%20specific%20%26quot%3Bceasefire%26quot%3B%20mention%20whereas%20the%20wording%20in%20the%20October%2027%20resolution%20was%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%2C%20durable%20and%20sustained%20humanitarian%20truce.%26quot%3B%20But%20India's%20larger%20demand%20in%20October%20seemed%20to%20have%20been%20to%20include%20a%20condemnation%20of%20Hamas%20as%20it%20had%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20Canada's%20amendment%20to%20the%20resolution%20that%20had%20asked%20specifically%20for%20condemning%20the%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20and%20that%20being%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20current%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20Deputy%20Permanent%20Representative%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20Yojna%20Patel%2C%20had%20mentioned%20in%20the%20explanation%20of%20the%20vote%20on%20October%2027%20that%20the%20October%207%20terror%20attacks%20were%20shocking%2C%20calling%20for%20the%20immediate%20release%20of%20the%20hostages.%20But%20the%20resolution%20moved%20by%20Jordan%20had%20made%20no%20mention%20of%20that.%20The%20resolution%20in%20October%20was%20passed%20with%20120%20votes%20in%20favour%2C%2014%20against%20and%2045%20abstentions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F2645kccs_israel-army-in-gaza_625x300_12_December_23.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20today's%20resolution%20had%20an%20overwhelming%20153%20nations%20in%20favour%20with%2010%20voting%20against%20and%2023%20abstentions.%20The%20resolution%20was%20passed%20by%20a%20large%20majority%2C%20securing%20the%20needed%20two-thirds%20of%20members%20and%20a%20round%20of%20applause.%20However%2C%20a%20UNGA%20resolution%20is%20legally%20non-binding%20but%20strongly%20reflects%20the%20sentiment%20of%20the%20world%20with%20each%20member%20country%20having%20one%20representative%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20unlike%20the%20UNSC%20which%20is%20more%20powerful%20as%20its%20resolutions%20are%20binding%20but%20has%20only%2015%20members%20with%20five%20permanent%20members%20having%20the%20veto%20power.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20long-standing%20debate%20that%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20UNSC%20doesn't%20reflect%20the%20current%20global%20realities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20stood%20out%20though%20was%20Canada's%20changed%20position.%20Like%20India%2C%20it%20changed%20from%20abstention%20on%20October%2027%20to%20voting%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution%20on%20Tuesday.%20But%20why%20the%20two%20are%20different%20is%20because%20India's%20vote%20on%20Tuesday%20is%20more%20consistent%20with%20its%20long-standing%20position%20on%20Palestine%20and%20Israel%2C%20but%20for%20Canada%2C%20which%20has%20always%20stood%20with%20Israel%2C%20the%20vote%20against%20it%20reflects%20a%20growing%20discomfort%20with%20Israel's%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20especially%20as%20the%20public%20sentiment%20in%20Canada%20has%20increasingly%20been%20on%20seeking%20ceasefire%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fk25ahv4_gaza_625x300_08_December_23.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20just%20hours%20before%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%2C%20a%20joint%20statement%20from%20Canada%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20New%20Zealand%20also%20specifically%20underlined%20this%20fact%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20alarmed%20at%20the%20diminishing%20safe%20space%20for%20civilians%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20price%20of%20defeating%20Hamas%20cannot%20be%20the%20continuous%20suffering%20of%20all%20Palestinian%20civilians.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20US%20voted%20on%20expected%20lines%20against%20the%20resolution%20despite%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20-%20just%20hours%20ahead%20of%20the%20voting%20-%20saying%20Israel%20was%20%26quot%3Blosing%20international%20support%26quot%3B.%20It%20was%20seen%20as%20an%20emerging%20rift%20over%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%2C%20but%20didn't%20get%20reflected%20in%20America's%20stand%20in%20the%20United%20Nations.%20However%2C%20despite%20America's%20backing%20of%20Israel%20in%20UN%2C%20the%20rift%20between%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20has%20for%20the%20first%20time%20been%20publicly%20revealed%20with%20Mr%20Biden's%20words%20that%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20starting%20to%20lose%20that%20support%20by%20the%20indiscriminate%20bombing%20that%20takes%20place%26quot%3B%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Maha%20Siddiqui%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20extensively%20reported%20on%20public%20policy%20and%20global%20affairs.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702491540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fq85i0t2_gaza_625x300_12_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcanada-signals-growing-moral-discomfort-among-israels-friends-4668965%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20opposed%20to%20an%20abstention%20in%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%20on%20October%2027%20related%20to%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%2C%20India%20voted%20in%20favour